{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# AdStackr Golden Path Architecture Version 2 – Simulation Demo
",
    "
",
    "This notebook drives the fake AdStackr + fake Google stack via HTTP:
",
    "- Connect (ingestion)
",
    "- Start a simulation run
",
    "- Generate impressions/clicks/conversions
",
    "- Run the semi-realistic optimizer
",
    "- Inspect before/after stats by segment and template
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import requests
",
    "import json
",
    "
",
    "BASE_URL = "http://localhost:8000"
",
    "ADSTACKR = f"{BASE_URL}/adstackr"
",
    "GOOGLE = f"{BASE_URL}/google"
",
    "
",
    "TENANT_ID = "demo-tenant"
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Seed fake Google with sample data
",
    "
",
    "For now, we seed the in-memory GoogleFake state by calling a small helper endpoint (or you can import and run Python directly if running in the same process).
",
    "
",
    "Here, we assume you run this notebook in the same environment and can call a small HTTP helper that seeds campaigns, line items, creatives, templates, and feed rows. If you haven't added such an endpoint yet, you can quickly add one later to `google_fake/api.py`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simple seeding via direct HTTP if you add a `/google/seed` endpoint.
",
    "# For now, we just check that the server is reachable.
",
    "
",
    "resp = requests.get(f"{BASE_URL}/")
",
    "print(resp.status_code, resp.json())
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If you want, you can manually populate GoogleFake's state by adding a `/seed` endpoint later. For demo purposes, you can also pre-populate it inside `google_fake/models.py` by editing the `state` object."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Call AdStackr /connect (fake ingestion)
",
    "
",
    "We send a fake connector config with minimal credentials and a few feed rows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "connector_payload = {
",
    "    "tenant_id": TENANT_ID,
",
    "    "dv360_credentials": {"project_id": "demo-project"},
",
    "    "cm360_credentials": {"profile_id": "12345"},
",
    "    "studio_credentials": {"user": "demo@example.com"},
",
    "    "feed_rows": [
",
    "        {"id": "row1", "segment_id": "seg_A", "headline": "Buy shoes", "image": "img1.jpg"},
",
    "        {"id": "row2", "segment_id": "seg_B", "headline": "Buy hats", "image": "img2.jpg"}
",
    "    ],
",
    "    "linked_campaign_id": "camp1"
",
    "}
",
    "
",
    "resp = requests.post(f"{ADSTACKR}/connect", json=connector_payload)
",
    "print(resp.status_code)
",
    "print(json.dumps(resp.json(), indent=2))
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Inspect catalog from AdStackr view
",
    "
",
    "This shows what AdStackr sees in the fake Google stack after ingestion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.get(f"{ADSTACKR}/catalog", params={"tenant_id": TENANT_ID})
",
    "print(resp.status_code)
",
    "catalog = resp.json()
",
    "print(json.dumps(catalog, indent=2))
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Start a simulation run
",
    "
",
    "We create a new `run_id` that tracks mappings and stats for a particular optimization run."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.post(f"{ADSTACKR}/sim/start", params={"tenant_id": TENANT_ID})
",
    "print(resp.status_code, resp.json())
",
    "run_id = resp.json()["run_id"]
",
    "run_id
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Run baseline traffic (before optimization)
",
    "
",
    "We send a number of simulated bid wins (impressions) into the system and let clicks/conversions occur randomly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.post(f"{ADSTACKR}/sim/step", params={"run_id": run_id, "n": 500})
",
    "print(resp.status_code, resp.json())
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Check status before optimization
",
    "
",
    "We look at impressions/clicks/conversions per segment/template before running the optimizer."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.get(f"{ADSTACKR}/sim/{run_id}/status")
",
    "print(resp.status_code)
",
    "before_opt = resp.json()
",
    "before_opt
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Run optimizer (epsilon-greedy on CTR)
",
    "
",
    "This updates the per-segment mapping to favor higher-CTR options."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.post(f"{ADSTACKR}/optimize", params={"run_id": run_id})
",
    "print(resp.status_code)
",
    "opt_changes = resp.json()
",
    "opt_changes
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Run more traffic after optimization
",
    "
",
    "We send more simulated impressions after the mappings have been updated."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.post(f"{ADSTACKR}/sim/step", params={"run_id": run_id, "n": 500})
",
    "print(resp.status_code, resp.json())
"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Check status after optimization
",
    "
",
    "Now we inspect the same status endpoint again to see how performance evolved per segment/template."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resp = requests.get(f"{ADSTACKR}/sim/{run_id}/status")
",
    "print(resp.status_code)
",
    "after_opt = resp.json()
",
    "after_opt
"
   ]
  }
 ],
